# Deployment Exclusion List
# ========================
# The canonical list of files/directories that are framework scaffolding
# and must NEVER be included in deployment artifacts.
#
# Syntax: .gitignore conventions (one pattern per line, # for comments).
#
# Usage:
#   rsync --exclude-from=.deployignore ./ _deploy/
#   Custom scripts can parse this file to filter deployable content.
#
# For Docker deployments, .dockerignore mirrors this file and is consumed
# natively by Docker during image builds.

# AI development framework
.claude/

# GitHub configuration (workflows, CODEOWNERS, PR template)
.github/

# Git and deployment meta files
.gitignore
.deployignore
.dockerignore

# Template and project documentation
README.md
INIT_INSTRUCTIONS.md
LICENSE

# Legacy and reference directories
CLAUDE_AI_INIT_PROJECT/
references/

# IDE and editor files (belt-and-suspenders — also in .gitignore)
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Project-specific exclusions
# Add lines below for files that exist in the repo but should not be deployed.
# Examples:
#   tests/
#   docs/
#   Makefile
#   *.md
#   scripts/
